1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:31,310 --> 00:01:36,009
[A Lonely Hero's Journey]

3
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:38,680
[Episode 34]

4
00:01:40,990 --> 00:01:41,590
Junsheng,

5
00:01:41,990 --> 00:01:42,990
go find Mrs. Wang.

6
00:01:45,750 --> 00:01:46,950
Haimo, stop packing.

7
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:48,870
Don't try to get rid of me!

8
00:01:56,170 --> 00:01:57,670
I know I've only been

9
00:01:58,490 --> 00:02:00,980
a temporary wife to you all these years.

10
00:02:01,950 --> 00:02:03,030
Now that we've won,

11
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:04,160
you want to ditch me.

12
00:02:05,170 --> 00:02:07,170
Listen up. No way!

13
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,509
What are you thinking?

14
00:02:11,150 --> 00:02:12,300
Let me show you something.

15
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:12,760
[Good Citizen Certificate]

16
00:02:12,910 --> 00:02:13,870
These are the Good Citizen Certificates

17
00:02:13,870 --> 00:02:15,640
I asked No. 90 to make for us secretly.

18
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:16,820
[Current address: 4 Baihua Lane, Suzhou]

19
00:02:16,150 --> 00:02:17,079
This one is mine.

20
00:02:17,270 --> 00:02:18,270
[Zhang Mengzhu]

21
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,460
This one is for you.

22
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:19,829
This is for Junsheng.

23
00:02:19,829 --> 00:02:20,960
All three certificates.

24
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:21,950
I was thinking

25
00:02:22,110 --> 00:02:24,070
that you and Junsheng could leave first,

26
00:02:24,070 --> 00:02:25,390
and I'd join you

27
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:27,310
after I finish up in a couple of days.

28
00:02:27,310 --> 00:02:28,030
Really?

29
00:02:30,430 --> 00:02:31,510
When have I ever lied to you?

30
00:02:31,510 --> 00:02:33,190
You didn't lie before,

31
00:02:34,190 --> 00:02:36,050
but over the past couple of years,

32
00:02:37,020 --> 00:02:39,090
you've become a very good liar.

33
00:02:40,620 --> 00:02:42,450
I don't like No. 90.

34
00:02:43,030 --> 00:02:45,310
I don't want you to go back to that place either.

35
00:02:45,310 --> 00:02:47,910
You've put your life on the line all these years

36
00:02:47,910 --> 00:02:50,900
and have come close to losing it several times.

37
00:02:51,430 --> 00:02:53,160
But who remembers you for that?

38
00:02:53,410 --> 00:02:55,000
Have they ever contacted you?

39
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,090
Stop it, will you?

40
00:02:58,190 --> 00:03:00,510
Okay, I'll leave it at that.

41
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,570
I know you have never forgotten her

42
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,850
in your heart all these years.

43
00:03:15,940 --> 00:03:17,430
I know it.

44
00:03:19,510 --> 00:03:20,930
I never expected

45
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:24,560
to hold the same place in your heart as she does.

46
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:28,490
But Yizhong,

47
00:03:30,829 --> 00:03:32,170
I'd be pleased

48
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:35,850
if you treated me

49
00:03:38,060 --> 00:03:40,190
even a tenth as well as you treated her.

50
00:03:44,940 --> 00:03:45,910
Stop it, will you?

51
00:03:45,910 --> 00:03:47,910
I'm afraid that if I don't say it now,

52
00:03:52,190 --> 00:03:53,720
I won't have a chance again.

53
00:03:59,070 --> 00:03:59,910
It won't.

54
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:08,260
Actually, I've been meaning to say this

55
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,770
for a long time.

56
00:04:13,430 --> 00:04:14,230
I feel much better

57
00:04:14,230 --> 00:04:15,890
having said it out loud today.

58
00:04:26,190 --> 00:04:26,880
Haimo.

59
00:04:29,260 --> 00:04:30,060
Look at me.

60
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:36,330
Look at me.

61
00:04:41,230 --> 00:04:43,400
I will live until that day arrives.

62
00:04:44,110 --> 00:04:46,000
I want to see those Japs

63
00:04:46,070 --> 00:04:47,930
get out of Suzhou with my own eyes!

64
00:04:48,150 --> 00:04:49,300
Trust me.

65
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:51,920
I'll come to you immediately

66
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:54,810
after I handle everything.

67
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:15,510
Come to us soon.

68
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:18,370
Go.

69
00:05:18,450 --> 00:05:19,610
You must be careful.

70
00:05:55,460 --> 00:05:58,240
[Gu Yanzhi]

71
00:06:07,430 --> 00:06:13,260
[Path to Freedom]

72
00:06:29,110 --> 00:06:30,390
Chief Gu, you're here.

73
00:06:38,570 --> 00:06:39,420
Chief Gu.

74
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:40,890
This is the prisoner who was transferred from Changshu

75
00:06:40,890 --> 00:06:43,010
at the specific request of Chief Xie.

76
00:06:43,590 --> 00:06:44,510
He also specifically said

77
00:06:44,510 --> 00:06:45,990
that no one could interrogate him

78
00:06:45,990 --> 00:06:46,720
until

79
00:06:46,790 --> 00:06:48,310
he came back from Nanjing.

80
00:06:51,790 --> 00:06:54,320
At No. 90, is Chief Gu in the primary position,

81
00:06:54,350 --> 00:06:55,830
or is it Xie?

82
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,000
Open the prison door!

83
00:06:59,130 --> 00:06:59,970
Okay.

84
00:07:01,230 --> 00:07:02,510
Not sharp.

85
00:07:02,550 --> 00:07:03,880
Enough. Don't be rough.

86
00:07:05,380 --> 00:07:05,790
Go!

87
00:07:08,190 --> 00:07:08,630
Go!

88
00:07:11,310 --> 00:07:11,750
Go.

89
00:07:23,430 --> 00:07:24,370
Chen Anliang.

90
00:07:25,790 --> 00:07:27,630
You're from Changshu?

91
00:07:30,790 --> 00:07:33,390
From the 51st Regiment of the 16th Brigade of the 6th Division

92
00:07:33,390 --> 00:07:34,650
of the New Fourth Army.

93
00:07:42,140 --> 00:07:44,110
Your hands seem quite delicate to me.

94
00:07:44,110 --> 00:07:46,110
They don't look like a cook's hands.

95
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:48,280
You're an educated person,

96
00:07:50,830 --> 00:07:52,040
35 years old.

97
00:07:52,230 --> 00:07:54,030
You can't be just an ordinary soldier

98
00:07:54,030 --> 00:07:55,630
in the New Fourth Army.

99
00:07:56,060 --> 00:07:58,790
You don't look like you're from the army, either.

100
00:08:02,890 --> 00:08:04,060
Let me guess.

101
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:07,110
Are you a regimental chief of operations

102
00:08:08,340 --> 00:08:09,800
or a political commissar?

103
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:17,800
Commissar Chen?

104
00:08:19,030 --> 00:08:20,160
Chief of Staff Chen.

105
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:22,040
I'll call you that for now.

106
00:08:22,860 --> 00:08:24,710
Among the vice division commanders in your 6th Division,

107
00:08:24,710 --> 00:08:26,440
is there one named Luo Wuqiang?

108
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,760
We're old friends.

109
00:08:32,169 --> 00:08:34,570
We had dealings before he turned to the CPC.

110
00:08:35,030 --> 00:08:35,650
Hit me.

111
00:08:38,710 --> 00:08:39,620
What a pity

112
00:08:40,309 --> 00:08:42,150
that Luo Wuqiang chose the wrong path later

113
00:08:42,150 --> 00:08:43,610
and joined your division.

114
00:08:43,950 --> 00:08:44,630
Hit me.

115
00:08:49,350 --> 00:08:50,310
Traitor!

116
00:08:54,230 --> 00:08:54,930
Chief! Chief!

117
00:08:54,930 --> 00:08:55,910
Chief!

118
00:08:57,630 --> 00:08:58,550
Take him to the Stump Execution Ground

119
00:08:58,550 --> 00:08:59,510
and shoot him!

120
00:08:59,630 --> 00:09:00,390
Take him away!

121
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:01,230
Yes! Go!

122
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:03,610
Stop!

123
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:05,190
Do you want to die?

124
00:09:06,550 --> 00:09:07,080
Get lost!

125
00:09:11,990 --> 00:09:13,110
Captain Zhang!

126
00:09:16,150 --> 00:09:17,790
Him, what's wrong?

127
00:09:19,990 --> 00:09:20,940
One of the New Fourth Army soldiers.

128
00:09:20,940 --> 00:09:22,000
Very bad.

129
00:09:22,420 --> 00:09:24,120
Going to kill him.

130
00:09:45,290 --> 00:09:46,640
The car is over there.

131
00:09:52,990 --> 00:09:53,750
Thank you.

132
00:09:55,380 --> 00:09:56,080
Go.

133
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:15,780
No, go back.

134
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:21,120
Captain Zhang, the Japanese won't let us pass.

135
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,860
They used to let us pass once they took a look.

136
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:26,840
What's going on now?

137
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:28,360
The new batch of Japs soldiers

138
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:29,780
doesn't look familiar either.

139
00:10:29,780 --> 00:10:30,870
I'll go take a look.

140
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:31,950
Jiping,

141
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,360
I'll go with you.

142
00:10:39,810 --> 00:10:41,610
You can't pass through here.

143
00:10:42,510 --> 00:10:44,510
I'm Gu Yizhong.

144
00:10:44,820 --> 00:10:47,310
Under Mr. Kondo's orders,

145
00:10:47,710 --> 00:10:49,640
we need to escort the criminal out.

146
00:10:50,070 --> 00:10:52,230
Please understand.

147
00:10:56,010 --> 00:10:59,250
[Chang Gate]

148
00:11:12,310 --> 00:11:13,720
Wait, wait.

149
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:15,740
Chief Gu,

150
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:18,100
are we really going to let this Mr. Si go?

151
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:19,040
If not,

152
00:11:19,830 --> 00:11:21,490
what do you want to do with him?

153
00:11:22,190 --> 00:11:23,650
In the current situation,

154
00:11:23,810 --> 00:11:25,670
if you dare to shoot Mr. Si...

155
00:11:26,670 --> 00:11:27,960
If the Japs lose,

156
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,560
what will you do

157
00:11:29,850 --> 00:11:32,250
when the New Fourth Army takes over Suzhou?

158
00:11:32,710 --> 00:11:34,520
Changjiu, let him go.

159
00:11:36,140 --> 00:11:38,470
But if we really let him go,

160
00:11:38,510 --> 00:11:40,190
what will we tell Xie Wenchao

161
00:11:40,190 --> 00:11:41,320
when he asks for him?

162
00:11:41,390 --> 00:11:42,450
I have my own way

163
00:11:42,490 --> 00:11:43,640
of dealing with Xie.

164
00:11:45,140 --> 00:11:46,080
But you,

165
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:48,880
you have to get your head around the current situation.

166
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:49,710
Soon, they will come after

167
00:11:49,710 --> 00:11:51,350
traitors like us.

168
00:11:51,790 --> 00:11:53,650
Isn't it good to leave us a way out?

169
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:55,560
Think about it.

170
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:58,480
Chief,

171
00:11:59,450 --> 00:12:00,860
whatever you say,

172
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:02,080
I'll listen to you.

173
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:04,760
Alright, go back with the car.

174
00:12:05,730 --> 00:12:06,700
Get in. Get in.

175
00:12:14,690 --> 00:12:16,090
I want to see Luo Wuqiang.

176
00:12:16,110 --> 00:12:17,970
I have an urgent military report.

177
00:12:20,750 --> 00:12:21,880
Hurry and go inside!

178
00:12:24,070 --> 00:12:24,770
Thank you so much.

179
00:12:24,770 --> 00:12:26,200
You must be tired

180
00:12:26,230 --> 00:12:27,710
from the long journey here.

181
00:12:27,710 --> 00:12:30,070
Hua, boil a pot of water

182
00:12:30,230 --> 00:12:31,030
and cook.

183
00:12:31,630 --> 00:12:32,960
I'm sorry to bother you.

184
00:12:33,070 --> 00:12:33,930
Don't say that.

185
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:36,360
We've been waiting for you since last year.

186
00:12:38,010 --> 00:12:38,950
Be careful.

187
00:12:40,590 --> 00:12:42,430
Living conditions in the countryside

188
00:12:42,430 --> 00:12:43,950
aren't as comfortable as in the city.

189
00:12:43,950 --> 00:12:45,590
Madam, the room is ready.

190
00:12:45,590 --> 00:12:46,550
Please come in.

191
00:12:46,550 --> 00:12:47,510
Thank you, Miss.

192
00:12:47,530 --> 00:12:48,020
You're welcome.

193
00:12:48,020 --> 00:12:48,950
Go close the door.

194
00:12:48,950 --> 00:12:49,470
Okay.

195
00:12:50,150 --> 00:12:50,870
Let me do it.

196
00:12:50,910 --> 00:12:51,630
No need.

197
00:12:51,630 --> 00:12:52,710
Come on, this room.

198
00:12:53,470 --> 00:12:54,270
Thank you.

199
00:12:58,030 --> 00:12:58,690
Here we are.

200
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:05,770
Easy, easy.

201
00:13:18,470 --> 00:13:19,270
Who are you?

202
00:13:20,030 --> 00:13:20,960
What do you want?

203
00:13:24,350 --> 00:13:26,430
I want to see Division Commander Luo, Luo Wuqiang.

204
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:27,160
Impossible.

205
00:13:28,110 --> 00:13:29,470
Chief of Staff Chen said

206
00:13:30,020 --> 00:13:31,820
you had important information.

207
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:33,970
I won't say anything

208
00:13:34,710 --> 00:13:35,750
until I see him.

209
00:13:36,030 --> 00:13:38,150
The troops have just moved.

210
00:13:38,270 --> 00:13:39,190
Moved to where?

211
00:13:39,220 --> 00:13:39,990
I don't know.

212
00:13:40,670 --> 00:13:43,420
I won't tell you, even if I know.

213
00:13:43,590 --> 00:13:45,850
If you have anything to report,

214
00:13:46,390 --> 00:13:49,190
I can help you pass it on to Division Commander Luo.

215
00:13:50,540 --> 00:13:51,870
You guessed correctly.

216
00:13:52,420 --> 00:13:54,350
I'm the Regimental Chief of Staff for the 16th Brigade of the 6th Division.

217
00:13:54,350 --> 00:13:56,550
I was injured in battle last month

218
00:13:56,650 --> 00:13:58,550
and fell into the clutches of the puppet army.

219
00:13:58,550 --> 00:13:59,750
No matter who you are,

220
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:02,120
thank you for saving me.

221
00:14:06,190 --> 00:14:09,720
Chief of Staff Chen, how long will it take you to find the troops?

222
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,490
Captain Jiang knows

223
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:13,380
the locations of troop shelters.

224
00:14:13,470 --> 00:14:14,600
In one or two days,

225
00:14:14,830 --> 00:14:17,960
I should be able to catch up with Division Commander Luo's troops.

226
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:19,220
Do you have any papers?

227
00:14:24,350 --> 00:14:25,470
Is this okay?

228
00:14:40,190 --> 00:14:41,110
Mrs. Gu.

229
00:14:42,710 --> 00:14:43,710
Mrs. Gu.

230
00:14:45,620 --> 00:14:47,630
We don't have anything fancy here in the countryside.

231
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:49,300
I've made some sweet boiled eggs for you.

232
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:50,360
Thank you, Mrs. Lu.

233
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,620
Don't say that.

234
00:14:53,030 --> 00:14:54,510
We can't have you here,

235
00:14:54,530 --> 00:14:55,430
even if we want to.

236
00:14:55,430 --> 00:14:57,240
It's our honor to have you here.

237
00:14:58,220 --> 00:14:59,860
Why isn't Mr. Gu here?

238
00:15:01,670 --> 00:15:02,350
He...

239
00:15:03,540 --> 00:15:05,340
He'll be here in a couple of days.

240
00:15:05,950 --> 00:15:08,010
He has something urgent to deal with.

241
00:15:08,130 --> 00:15:09,120
That's good.

242
00:15:09,470 --> 00:15:10,660
When Mr. Gu comes,

243
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:12,420
your family will be reunited.

244
00:15:13,030 --> 00:15:14,230
Eat it while it's hot.

245
00:15:18,370 --> 00:15:19,830
[To the New Fourth Army: send troops as soon as you receive the letter]

246
00:15:23,580 --> 00:15:27,390
[Xiao Ruo...]

247
00:15:30,230 --> 00:15:32,610
[Xiao Ruotong's friend]

248
00:15:36,850 --> 00:15:37,920
This is urgent.

249
00:15:38,070 --> 00:15:39,200
I'm counting on you.

250
00:15:39,310 --> 00:15:40,670
I'll go to the troop now.

251
00:15:41,420 --> 00:15:42,970
You can rest here tonight

252
00:15:43,110 --> 00:15:44,390
and go back to Suzhou tomorrow morning.

253
00:15:44,390 --> 00:15:44,990
No.

254
00:15:45,510 --> 00:15:46,640
I have to leave tonight.

255
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:47,530
See you,

256
00:15:48,410 --> 00:15:49,290
Comrade Gu.

257
00:15:52,670 --> 00:15:53,550
Comrade Chen.

258
00:16:00,510 --> 00:16:02,630
Comrade Gu, I'll only see you off here.

259
00:16:02,630 --> 00:16:03,670
Follow this road,

260
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:04,960
and you'll reach the main road soon.

261
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:06,000
Follow the main road,

262
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,110
and you will arrive in Suzhou shortly.

263
00:16:08,110 --> 00:16:09,110
Take this.

264
00:16:12,550 --> 00:16:13,430
Take care.

265
00:17:46,390 --> 00:17:50,510
Forward to Captain Zhang, Zhang Jiping,

266
00:17:50,870 --> 00:17:53,670
at the Political Security Bureau, Suzhou Branch.

267
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:21,980
Deputy Chief Xie,

268
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:25,800
why are you pointing a gun at me

269
00:18:26,550 --> 00:18:27,670
in the early morning?

270
00:18:27,670 --> 00:18:29,000
Your lantern

271
00:18:29,270 --> 00:18:30,600
has run out of kerosene,

272
00:18:32,460 --> 00:18:34,990
and your shoes are caked with thick black mud.

273
00:18:36,940 --> 00:18:38,150
You must have done

274
00:18:38,990 --> 00:18:41,190
a lot of walking last night, didn't you?

275
00:18:41,940 --> 00:18:42,970
Yeah.

276
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:45,470
I was pleasantly surprised by the beautiful scenery

277
00:18:45,470 --> 00:18:46,530
outside of Suzhou.

278
00:18:47,670 --> 00:18:49,130
Don't point your gun at me.

279
00:18:50,510 --> 00:18:51,510
Deputy Chief Xie,

280
00:18:52,010 --> 00:18:53,910
have you heard of the verse

281
00:18:54,230 --> 00:18:56,030
"The night fair's bright as day;

282
00:18:56,070 --> 00:18:58,330
Outside temples boats stay" by Du Xunhe?

283
00:18:59,710 --> 00:19:01,630
I don't read much.

284
00:19:02,430 --> 00:19:05,560
I only know, "Beyond the city wall, from the Temple of Hanshan;

285
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:09,160
Bells break the ship-borne roamer's dream and midnight still."

286
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:11,160
That's a good line as well.

287
00:19:12,380 --> 00:19:14,910
